      {
        "id": 2488285,
        "name": "Dennis Atick",
        "username": "Dennis_Atick",
        "avatar_template": "/user_avatar/www.wineberserkers.com/dennis_atick/{size}/429_2.png",
        "created_at": "2018-09-23T15:12:48.000Z",
        "cooked": "<p>Still waiting for it to feel like I\u2019m not living too close to the sun, so its been a a lot sparkling wine and Chablis lately. Tried to coax fall along yesterday with some Beaujolais. This Foillard is screaming good in '16.</p>\n<ul>\n<li>\n<a href=\"https://www.cellartracker.com/note.asp?iWine=2755587&amp;iNote=7249969\"><strong>2016 Yvon M\u00e9tras Fleurie Le Printemps</strong></a> <em>- France, Burgundy, Beaujolais, Fleurie (9/23/2018)</em><br>\nDelicate as Fleurie can be. Light red to translucent pink. Floral and herbal, slightest bit of funk, there\u2019s certainly an interesting nose here. Leans to springtime. Clean strawberry and pomegranate flavors. It is light on the palate and easy to drink, it tastes like fresh pressed juice. Hiding nothing, it seems. Pales a bit to the Foillard Py next to it. Still a good drink. Clean by Metras standards.</li>\n<li>\n<a href=\"https://www.cellartracker.com/note.asp?iWine=2847259&amp;iNote=7247740\"><strong>2016 Jean Foillard Morgon C\u00f4te du Py</strong></a> <em>- France, Burgundy, Beaujolais, Morgon (9/22/2018)</em><br>\nTerrific young CdP from Foillard. Floral and wet rock (life after it rains) and sandalwood spice nose. Juicy cranberry-ish fruit, that is crunchy and so light weight, the palate texture is like silk. So smooth. This is a hard wine to put down, so damn drinkable. Finishes cool and long. Such energy and no harm in drinking now, but probably has a nice long life ahead.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><em>Posted from <a href=\"https://www.cellartracker.com/\">CellarTracker</a></em></p>",
