        "created_at": "2018-09-23T15:53:12.000Z",
        "cooked": "<aside class=\"quote no-group\" data-post=\"3\" data-topic=\"145956\">\n<blockquote>\n<p>Thanks, William. Thanks for the reminder on the hail, didn\u2019t even think about that yesterday. I hear you on the Foillard. Really good wine. Still have a couple, but now I\u2019m out for for more.</p>\n</blockquote>\n</aside>\n<p>I bought a bunch in Beaune for 20 euros a piece, should have bought all they had. But there will be other vintages.</p>\n<p>Daniel Bouland made some really good 2016s too, definitely worth looking for the Corcelette bottlings and the Delys Vieilles Vignes.</p>\n<p>Now I\u2019m waiting to see what 2017 M\u00e9tras I\u2019ll be able to get\u2026</p>",
